>> title: Cheese Quesadillas with Leftover Taco Beef
>> cuisine: Mexican
>> tags: quick-cook, kid-friendly, leftovers
>> servings: 2

-- Leftover night. The lesson: patience makes the crust - medium heat and
-- don't rush the flip. Cheese on both sides of the filling is the glue.

Warm the leftover taco beef (about 1 1/2 cups from taco night) in the #microwave{} or a small pan.

Heat a large dry #skillet{} over medium. Lay in a @flour tortilla{1}(large burrito-size). Scatter @monterey jack cheese{1/2%cup}(shredded) over the whole tortilla, spoon a quarter of the beef over ONE half, and top the beef with a little more cheese.

When the cheese starts melting and the underside is golden-brown spotted (2-3 minutes - peek with a spatula), fold the empty half over the beef half and press gently.

Flip once and cook 1-2 more minutes until both sides are crisp. Rest it 2 minutes on a cutting board - resting keeps the cheese in - then cut into wedges with a #pizza cutter{}.

Repeat with @flour tortillas{3}(large) and @monterey jack cheese{1 1/2%cups}(shredded) for the rest.

Serve with @salsa{1/2%cup} and @sour cream{1/4%cup}.
